[SN]TITLE[SN]
Accident closes A76 between Thornhill and Carronbridge

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A major road between Dumfries and Kilmarnock was closed for more than eight hours, following a serious accident.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
It happened on the A76 between Thornhill and Carronbrige shortly after 01:00.
A 40-mile diversion was put in place before the road re-opened at 09:15.
Police Scotland has not released any details about the vehicles involved or any casualties.
